Data Collection
The system collects input from the user:
Daily study hours
Sleep hours
Number of assignments
Social/relaxation time
Parameter Evaluation
Each input is analyzed using predefined conditions:
Higher study hours → increases stress
Less sleep → increases stress
More assignments → increases stress
Less social time → increases stress
Stress Score Calculation
Each parameter is assigned a score (1 to 3) based on its impact
All scores are added to compute a total stress score
Stress Level Classification
Based on the total score:
Low Stress → Score ≤ 5
Moderate Stress → Score between 6 and 9
High Stress → Score > 9
Result Display
The system displays the stress score
It also shows the stress level with a suggestion message
Conclusion/Output
Helps students understand their stress condition
Encourages better time management, rest, and relaxation
